{
  "texts": [
    "To achieve that, COMPER first stores the transitions together with estimated Q-values into a structure named Transition Memory (T M), which is similar to a traditional replay buf- fer, except for the presence of the Q-value and the identification and indexing of Similar Transitions Sets (ST).",
    "After that, the similarities between the transitions stored in T M can be explored to generate a more compact version of it -the RT M.",
    "Then, the transitions (s t, a t, r t, s t+1) ∼ U (RT M) are drawn uniformly from RT M and used to minimize the following loss function,",
    "in which Q(s t, a t, Θ i) is a Q-function approximated by a CNN parameterized by Θ i at i-th iteration.",
    "QT (τ t, Ω) is a Q-target function approximated by an LSMT and parameterized by Ω."
  ]
}